article.headline: California 68, USC 59
article.story:
BERKELEY, Calif. (AP) -- Jackie Sanchez scored all 11 of her
points in the final 6:45 to lead California to a 68-59 win over
Southern California on Saturday.

The Golden Bears (10-15, 3-13 Pac-10) snapped an 11-game losing
streak by coming back from a 10-point deficit to upset the Trojans
(14-11, 11-6).

Nihan Anaz had a game-high 21 points for California and Leigh
Gregory added 15, but it was Sanchez, averaging just 4.2 points a
game, who took over down the stretch.

Sanchez' 3-point play with 6:45 left gave Cal a 54-49 lead.
Later she hit two free throws with 3:41 to play, extending the
Bears' lead to seven and helping to seal the win.

Ebony Hoffman scored 15 points and Rometra Craig had 12 for USC,
which led by as many as 10 in the first half, and led 30-24 at the
break.

But the Trojans shot just 11-of-37 from the field in the second
half to let Cal climb back into the game.

Southern California suffered a serious blow to its hopes of
making the NCAA tournament, and may now have to win the Pac-10
conference tournament to earn a bid.
